text: Oh It's good to be here alone in front of six hundred thousand people. It's a large nation but it's still weak, still very weak. It needs to get a lot stronger before it can claim a right to a land
I've looked into the mirrors in numberless places
They all smile back at me with the most troublesome faces.
The cards that they dealt me, no there weren't any aces
And the horses just don't listen to me at the races.
There's still one or two of us, walking the street
No arrows of direction painted under our feet
No angels to warn us away from the heat
And no honey to keep us where it is sweet
